General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 of the top-two, same-day primary runoff method shall apply in the same manner to the new
2 threshold.
3 (e) Process to Request Top-Two, Same-Day Runoff. – To request a top-two runoff in a
4 primary, the political party shall file a written request with the Executive Director of the State
5 Board within 21 days after the filing deadline. To request a top-two runoff for a primary in a
6 single-county State Senate or State House of Representatives district or for a county office, the
7 request shall be submitted to the respective county board of elections within 21 days after the
8 filing deadline."
9 SECTION 2. The State Board of Elections (State Board) shall develop an optimal
10 method for conducting and counting a top-two, same-day runoff primary. The State Board shall
11 research and design an easy-to-understand ballot for voters to rank their preferred candidates.
12 The ballot design must interwork with various voting equipment used by different jurisdictions
13 in the State. It should afford voters an easy transition to other races that use the standard voting
14 method. Additionally, the State Board shall develop a program of voter education for using the
15 system.
16 SECTION 3. There is appropriated from the General Fund to the State Auditor,
17 pursuant to Section 3A.2 of S.L. 2024-57, for the State Board of Elections (State Board) the sum
18 of four hundred ten thousand dollars ($410,000) nonrecurring for each year of the 2025-2027
19 fiscal biennium for implementation, education, and training needed in the development of the
20 optional top-two, same-day primary runoff method as provided by this act. The State Board shall
21 allocate funds appropriated pursuant to this section as follows:
22 (1) The sum of two hundred ten thousand dollars ($210,000) nonrecurring for
23 each year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium for information technology
24 development work related to election reporting and ballot changes to integrate
25 into the current Statewide Elections Information Management System
26 (SEIMS).
27 (2) The sum of two hundred thousand dollars ($200,000) nonrecurring for each
28 year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium for statewide education and training
29 requirements related to implementing the provisions of this act.
30 SECTION 4. Section 3 of this act becomes effective July 1, 2025. The remainder of
31 this act becomes effective December 1, 2025, and applies to elections held on or after that date.
